<subSubSection id="C301655DFFD1AD0540853396FCACF91B" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA436D6FFD1AD0540853396FF51FA63" blockId="6.[151,1436,1182,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD0540853396FEA1FB02" bold="true" box="[151,273,1182,1207]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing length of male 
<quantity id="4CE39B33FFD1AD0542233396FD7AFB03" box="[561,714,1182,1206]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.89" metricValueMin="3.61" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="3.75" valueMax="3.89" valueMin="3.61">3.61–3.89 cm</quantity>
(mean = 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD0543263396FCD8FB03" box="[820,872,1182,1206]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="3.77">3.77</number>
, n = 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD05438F3396FC1CFB03" box="[925,940,1182,1206]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="5.0">5</number>
), and female 
<quantity id="4CE39B33FFD1AD0544563396FB6DFB03" box="[1092,1245,1182,1206]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.205" metricValueMax="4.32" metricValueMin="4.09" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="4.205" valueMax="4.32" valueMin="4.09">4.09–4.32 cm</quantity>
(mean = 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD0545553396FADDFB03" box="[1351,1389,1182,1206]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="4.2">4.2</number>
, n = 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD05408533CAFF17FB6F" box="[151,167,1218,1242]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="3.0">3</number>
). Dorsal forewing basal to medial areas pale yellow, notably lighter in color than 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD05442B33CCFB26FB6E" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1081,1174,1219,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD05442B33CCFB26FB6E" box="[1081,1174,1219,1243]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD0544DF33CCFAD5FB6E" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1229,1381,1219,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD0544DF33CCFAD5FB6E" box="[1229,1381,1219,1243]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and usually outlined distally by an orange tinge. Ventral forewing brown postmedial band often thinner than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD05459633E0FF65FA96" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD05459633E0FF65FA96" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD05411F3204FE16FA96" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[269,422,1291,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD05411F3204FE16FA96" box="[269,422,1291,1315]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; this band is thicker from M 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD0542E33202FD4BFA97" box="[753,763,1290,1314]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
to the middle of the Cu 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD05441D3202FBA8FA97" box="[1039,1048,1290,1314]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
cell, becoming thinner and with a zigzag pattern from there to 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD0541CC3226FE57FAF3" box="[478,487,1326,1350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
A+ 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD05421C3226FDACFAF3" box="[526,540,1326,1350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
A (the zigzag pattern corresponds to the edge of the yellow area on the dorsal surface). Dorsal hind wing yellow area pale such that the underside pattern is visible dorsally, brown band form the postmedial to marginal area narrower than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD0542813270FD5FFA3B" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[659,751,1398,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD0542813270FD5FFA3B" box="[659,751,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD0543373270FC0DFA3B" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[805,957,1398,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD0543373270FC0DFA3B" box="[805,957,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, usually interspersed by pale yellow spots. Females similar to males except for the better defined dorsal marginal and submarginal pale yellow spots on both wings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA436D6FFD1AD0540D732EAFCACF91B" blockId="6.[151,1436,1182,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD0540D732EAFE8AFA4E" bold="true" box="[197,314,1506,1531]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Given the smaller size of this species, both the male and female genitalia are proportionately smaller than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD0541943100FE53F9AB" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[390,483,1542,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD0541943100FE53F9AB" box="[390,483,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD05420A3100FD01F9AB" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[536,689,1542,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD05420A3100FD01F9AB" box="[536,689,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male specimens (three dissections, two without locality data) varied in the width of the distal half of the valva, and also the number of subterminal spines at the dorsal edge (
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD1AD05457C3122FF15F9D3" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD0540853146FF15F9D3" box="[151,165,1614,1638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). Female sterigma with long lateral arms, and a longer and narrower midline lobe than those in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD05451D3158FADDF9D3" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1295,1389,1614,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD05451D3158FADDF9D3" box="[1295,1389,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD054085317CFE9FF93E" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[151,303,1651,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD054085317CFE9FF93E" box="[151,303,1651,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(but only one female was dissected). Corpus bursa oval shaped, with paired signa, and constricted at the meeting point with the narrow ductus bursa (
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD1AD0542A4319EFD4AF91B" box="[694,762,1686,1710]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD0542F9319EFD4AF91B" box="[747,762,1686,1710]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
