</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C301655DFFD1AD0440D731D6FC63FEA9" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA436D6FFD1AD0540D731D6FEE7F847" blockId="6.[151,1436,1182,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD0540D731D6FE43F942" bold="true" box="[197,499,1758,1783]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Variation and subspecies.</emphasis>
Some variation in wing color has been identified, such as the size of the pale yellow spots at the dorsal hind wing margin (see males in 
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD1AD0542DB300AFCB6F8AF" box="[713,774,1794,1818]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD0542EE300AFCB6F8AF" box="[764,774,1794,1818]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A and D, and females in 
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD1AD05440C300AFBECF8AF" box="[1054,1116,1794,1818]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD054443300AFBECF8AF" box="[1105,1116,1794,1818]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B and C). As noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B27FFD1AD05454C300AFE84F88B" author="Fruhstorfer" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD0540E0302EFE9CF88B" box="[242,300,1830,1854]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
the association of wing color with subspecific forms seems arbitrary. This probably led to Casagrande’s (
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD0541193042FEF6F8D7" box="[267,326,1866,1890]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2004.0">2004</number>
) proposal that 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD0542103044FC2FF8D7" authority="Butler, 1874" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1874" box="[514,927,1866,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bassus" subSpecies="luteipenis">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD0542103044FD5DF8D6" box="[514,749,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. bassus luteipenis</emphasis>
(Butler, 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD05434C3042FC28F8D7" box="[862,920,1866,1890]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1874.0">1874</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
be considered a synonym of the nominal subspecies. We note that two females from Campos do Jordão, São Paulo state (
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD1AD0544543066FB39F833" box="[1094,1161,1902,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD05446C3066FB39F833" box="[1150,1161,1902,1926]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C), appear to be darker orange in color, and with larger pale yellow spots at the dorsal hind wing margin than those from more southern localities (
<figureCitation id="13202A53FFD1AD05411E30BEFEFCF87B" box="[268,332,1974,1998]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD324F1FFD1AD05415330BEFEFCF87B" box="[321,332,1974,1998]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Mirna Casagrande (pers. comm.) notes that females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD1AD0543FA30B0FBE3F87B" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1000,1107,1974,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD1AD0543FA30B0FBE3F87B" box="[1000,1107,1974,1999]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may vary in color within the same population.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA436D6FFD0AD0440D73790FC63FEA9" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0440D73790FE7AFF05" bold="true" box="[197,458,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Natural history notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B27FFD0AD0441C0379FFD12FF1A" author="Fruhstorfer" box="[466,674,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number id="3DD324F1FFD0AD04424D379FFD29FF1A" box="[607,665,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04435B3791FC03FF05" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[841,947,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04435B3791FC03FF05" box="[841,947,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is commonly found with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD0444C43791FA83FF05" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1238,1331,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0444C43791FA83FF05" box="[1238,1331,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that unlike the latter, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04414937B5FE77FF61" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[347,455,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04414937B5FE77FF61" box="[347,455,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“ventures even in the greatest heat of the day on to sunny grass-lands with scattered bushes.” Andre Freitas (pers. comm.) observed 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD0442AC37E9FC9CFF4D" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[702,812,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD0442AC37E9FC9CFF4D" box="[702,812,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ovipositing on grass in Capão Bonito (Fazenda Intervales), São Paulo state, but the early stages of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D55FFD0AD04428F360DFCB7FEA9" authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[669,775,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAC4FFD0AD04428F360DFCB7FEA9" box="[669,775,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remain unknown.
</paragraph>
